no bigger mana pool<br>
no faster mana regen (sigh)<br>
<br>
guess all we are left with is spell efficiency and/or resistances<br>
<br>
new spell:  channel balefire<br>
<br>
channels 3 elements (fire, cold, magic) from all caster classes in group (people with mana) THROUGH a wizard to focus a beam of balefire (yes, shamelessly &quot;borrowed&quot; from Wheel of Time) on a monster.<br>
<br>
details:<br>
<br>
-mob must save vs. all 3 elements to avoid damage, if he fails 1 resist, he recieves full damage.<br>
<br>
-the spell drains 500 mana from all casters in group.<br>
<br>
-it is a 50 level single target dot damage =<br>
<br>
50*C*((L-40)/10) per tick for 30 ticks<br>
<br>
C=Number of casters in group<br>
L=Level of wizard casting<br>
<br>
-message:  A %t writhes in agony as he is set ablaze with balefire<br>
<br>
-*optional (graphic):  bright fluctuating red/blue/yellow ray comes from each caster to wizard, and then bright white thick ray from wizard to mob<br>
<br>
end result:<br>
<br>
-hardly resisted<br>
-with 6 casters, and level 60 wizard = 18k damage over 3 minutes for 3000 mana<br>
-with 6 casters, and level 50 wizard = 9k damage over 3 minutes for 3000 mana<br>
-with 1 caster, and level 50 wizard = 1500 damage over 3 minutes for 500 mana<br>
-useless solo (make verant and necro's happy)<br>
-gives wiz enough time to cast concussion a few times during<br>
-not useful in normal dungeon fodder, too long of a dot<br>
-mainly useful on big Velious mobs, that take a while to take down.<br>
-A wiz using this will not run out of mana very easily<br>
-Only useful if a &quot;caster team&quot; strategy is used.  A group of 5 wiz and 1 cleric would do 90k per 3 minutes if they could stay alive <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I know this will never happen, and I retired my wiz anyway, but it's fun to come here and dream *sigh*.<br>
<br>
-Lifty Swiftpocket<br>
